    "However, DFT operates in the complex domain, introducing potential computational overhead and numerical instability (Press, 2007), particularly in large-scale models (Gao et al., 2024).",
    "Such numerical inaccuracies inevitably degrade the performance.",
    "Moreover, the asymmetry between DFT and its inverse (iDFT) complicates forward and backward transformations, increasing computational intensity.",
    "To address these challenges, we propose a novel fine-tuning framework, Sparse Spectrum Adaptation via Discrete Hartley Transform (SSH).",
    "The advantage of leveraging DHT over DFT (Gao et al., 2024) is twofold."
